stract":[{"type":"text","text":"Iterating over a sequence of values over time is now as easy as writing a “for” loop. Find out how the new AsyncSequence protocol enables a natural, simple syntax for iterating over anything from notifications to bytes being streamed from a server. We’ll also show you how to adapt existing code to provide asynchronous sequences of your own."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10058-Meet-AsyncSequence"}}}